
	<sn><md>### Atmospheric Chemistry Syllabus{.fg-red .text-center}

| **Topic**                                  | **Subtopics**                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
|--------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Description of the Atmosphere              | - Composition of the air close to the earth’s surface, variations with height, latitude, season, and time.<br>- Mass of the atmosphere.<br>- Layers of the atmosphere.                                       |
| Solar Radiation and the Global Energy Budget | - Solar energy and principles of electromagnetic waves.<br>- Radiation transfer from the sun to earth.<br>- Factors affecting incoming solar radiation.<br>- Solar radiation budget.<br>- Factors affecting temperature variation. |
| Atmospheric Moisture Budget                | - Components of the global hydrological cycle.<br>- Changes of state of water.<br>- Humidity and condensation.<br>- Cloud types and precipitation.<br>- Air stability and instability.                        |
| Air Pressure and Winds                     | - Wind pressure and causes of variation (vertical and horizontal).<br>- Forces acting upon the wind.<br>- Global wind belts.<br>- Wind classification.                                                       |
| Global Air Circulation                     | - Circulation in vertical and horizontal planes.<br>- Monsoon circulation.<br>- Tropical cyclones and El Niño-Southern Oscillation (ENSO) events.                                                             |
| Atmospheric Chemistry                      | - Effects of atmospheric motions on chemistry.<br>- Half-life, residence time, and renewal time of chemicals.<br>- Chemical and photochemical reactions.<br>- Interaction of radiation with trace gases.      |
| Atmospheric Aerosols                       | - Airborne particulate matter: size, sources, concentration.<br>- Chemical composition, transformation, and transport of aerosols.<br>- Residence time and sink of aerosol particles.                         |
